   01/03/2018

Monitoring of the study

   This study was monitored by various bodies, both internal (internal
   steering committee) and external (Steering Committee and Scientific
   Committee) to the Agency.
     * The Steering Committee comprises the supervisory ministries
       involved in the project and the study’s various partner
       laboratories. Its purpose is to monitor the study’s progress and
       make choices about its major strategic themes.
     * The Scientific Committee is made up of experts from outside the
       Agency with complementary skills related to the assessment of
       health risks and the specific characteristics of the population of
       young children. This committee is consulted on the scientific
       aspects of the programme, in particular on the assessment of
       exposure.
     * In addition, the decision was made to set up two working groups,
       made up of scientific experts, who will work respectively on the
       quality of the analytical data from the contamination results and
       the health-based guidance values concerning young children aged 0-3
       years, which will be used in the study.
     * Finally, all the study findings will be presented to and validated
       by ANSES’s various expert committees (CESs) according to their
       respective spheres of competence. The establishment of these expert
       groups means that the scientific aspects of this study can benefit
       from the views of various experts on a given issue, with different
       opinions being expressed.

